President Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of New Jersey due to severe storm and flooding that occurred from July 14 to July 15, 2023. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Robert Little III of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made if requested by the state and warranted by damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.